<h3>Exercises</h3>

	<p>
		There will be <strong>8 exercises</strong> worth <strong>5 points each</strong>. Students will submit work files to the specified dropbox each week.
	</p>

<h3>Projects</h3>

	<p>
		Projects are longer term, in-depth, self-directed assignments used to explore and execute a non-academic design problem or series of problems. Significant research and development is required. To succeed, combine learned mechanics and principles, review and expand upon content and individual artistic expression.
	</p>
	
	<p>
		You will create your own artwork responding to your research and learned skills with creative freedom. An in-depth written self assessment reflecting on the process and presentation will be completed with each project.
	</p>
	
	<p>
		There are <strong>5 projects</strong> for this course worth <strong>10 points each</strong>. Each project will expand the studentâ€™s knowledge of an important aspect of Adobe Photoshop. Projects are graded on application of subject matter, appropriate use of the software and creativity.
	</p>
	
<h3>Final Project</h3>	

	<p>
	    There is <strong>1 final project</strong> for this course that is worth <strong>30 points</strong>. The final project will require you to use most if not all of the techniques you learn throughout the course.
	</p>
	
